soldiers at the us navy base at guantanamo 
cuba fired two shots thursday at cuban sentry posts breaking 
glass but causing no injuries the official news agency prensa 
latina said 
the news agency quoted a ministry statement as saying one shot 
was fired at 10 am est at sentry post 17 and a second at 1 pm 
at post 18 
lt cmdr ken satterfield a spokesman in washington for the 
pentagon said we received no reports of any such incident 
both shots shattered glass in the posts the agency said in the 
dispatch monitored in mexico the direction indicated the shots 
were fired from american post 13 the agency quoted the note as 
saying 
these actions are even more serious and of unpredictable 
consequences because the two shots hit the guardposts and could 
have wounded and even assassinated any of the soldiers who were on 
guard duty the agency quoted the note as saying 
the note said the last similar incident was aug 21 1987 when 
shots were fired from american post 18 on a cuban observation post 
it noted the incident occurred as the country was holding 
funerals for more than 2000 cuban soldiers and civilian 
technicians killed in angola and other foreign conflicts the past 
14 years 
the ministry said it was not an accident that these vulgar and 
dangerous provocations by yankee soldiers occurred precisely 
today 
