<TEXT>
china plans to shut down 10 percent of its 
newspapers and publishing houses targeting for closure those 
printing pornography or material critical of the communist party 
the official xinhua news agency said today 
the agency quoted the current issue of china cultural news as 
saying newspaper and magazine offices that publish pornographic 
stories or articles running counter to the party line will lose 
their licenses 
the press and publications administration will also merge 
newspapers and periodicals that are similar in content it said 
the report said china has 1600 newspapers 3000 social science 
periodicals and 500 publishing houses many are similar in nature 
and have few readers 
in the past year particularly after communist leaders used 
troops to crush the prodemocracy movement in june the government 
has moved to consolidate and exert greater control over the 
publishing industry 
millions of publications have been confiscated and destroyed in 
a nationwide antipornography campaign and a number of publications 
that sympathized with the prodemocracy movement such as 
shanghais world economic herald have been shut down or revamped 
li ruihuan the politburo standing committee member in charge of 
propaganda and cultural affairs said recently that many 
publications were being turned out that advocated bourgeois 
liberalization or western ideas 
he said such publications were full of seductive and poisonous 
material especially harmful to young people and it was high 
time to solve all these problems 
</TEXT>
