communist political and economic systems the opposite was true for 
eastern europe and for the soviet union 
seventyfive percent believed some of the eastern european 
countries are moving away from communist economies up from 47 
percent in march and 70 percent believed some of eastern europe 
was dropping the communist system more than double the number in 
march 
