<TEXT>
the soviet union can now launch groundattack 
jets from its first fullscale aircraft carrier a naval aviation 
advance that the us navy says holds the potential for offensive 
use 
the development came only days before mikhail s gorbachev 
pressed president bush on naval arms control issues at the malta 
summit 
the us navy confirmed on wednesday that the 65000ton tbilisi 
aircraft carrier had launched and recovered three fighter jets 
during trials in the black sea the mig29 fulcrum a su27 
flanker and the su25 frogfoot ground attack aircraft 
the tbilisis capabilities are a marked advance over the much 
smaller kievclass carrier which is capable of transporting only 
helicopters and jumpjets 
while the tbilisis sea trials are not unexpected navy 
officials pointed to the type of aircraft used on the carrier as 
interesting as well as the timing of the event 
they are way ahead of schedule said one navy officer who 
spoke on condition he not be identified by name 
use of an aircraft carrier vastly improves soviet tactical 
aviation capabilities allowing fighter jets to be launched far 
beyond the range of soviet borders 
the tbilisi is the first of its class while two others are 
under construction 
the ship uses a ski jump bow to launch aircraft and not the 
highpowered catapults that hurl jets from us carriers but the 
soviets do use the arresting wires that stop planes as they land on 
the deck just as the american carriers do 
the navy in a statement pointing to the ships offensive 
capabilities said 
the soviets have insisted that the tbilisi is intended 
for defensive purposes only nonetheless the demonstrated 
capability of the tbilisi to accommodate a variant of one of the 
soviet unions principal groundattack aircraft the frogfoot 
shows a potential for offensive operations 
