for congress mayor kathy whitmire has endorsed his bid for 
congress and helped him raise money 
washington and hall agree many issues both favor increased 
funding to battle drug trafficking and abuse and for health care 
to the poor and elderly and military cutbacks in central america 
what differences there are largely is a matter of style 
says franklin jones a political scientist at texas southern 
university washington comes off as the more grassroots kinds of 
campaigner more of the peoples candidate while hall has the 
more polished image as the sort of professional candidate but 
both of them are extremely professional and longterm political 
people 
