prime minister vp singh visited 
sikhisms holiest shrine the golden temple on thursday in a major 
initiative by his government to end the lingering secessionist 
campaign by sikh militants 
it was the first visit by a prime minister to the golden temple 
in more than five years since shortly after a bloody army raid 
that led to the assassination of prime minister indira gandhi 
too much bloodshed has taken place the hindu prime minister 
told about 20000 sikhs inside the 14th century shrine the time 
has come to win the hearts of the people 
in new delhi a judge formally dropped charges against four 
sikhs accused of participating in the oct 31 1984 assassination 
of mrs gandhi 
mrs gandhi was shot and killed by two sikh bodyguards angered 
by the army attack she ordered on the golden temple in june 1984 to 
drive out sikh militants using it as a base 
one assassin was shot and killed by security men the other was 
convicted along with an accomplice and both were hanged in january 
conspiracy charges were later filed against four other sikhs 
last week the government said it would withdraw the charges in a 
conciliatory move toward the sikh community 
one does wonder why the move was not made earlier said 
judge jaspal singh himself a sikh in ordering the charges dropped 
all sikhs and many hindus use the name singh which means lion 
two of the sikhs accused of conspiracy were elected to 
parliament in last months general elections in which vp singh 
and his national front coalition prevented rajiv gandhi mrs 
gandhis son and successor from returning to power 
singh was sworn in as prime minister saturday and said solving 
the sikh dispute in the northern state of punjab would be one of 
