total lack of bodyguards who surrounded gandhi during his public 
appearances singh traveled in an open jeep from amritsars raja 
sansi airport to the temple after refusing to sit in a bulletproof 
sedan 
your love to me is my security the prime minister told the 
gathering at the golddomed temple i have not come here for any 
political or governmental purposes i have come to perform prayers 
in the holy shrine so that peace and normalcy can be restored 
mrs gandhi was the last prime minister to visit the temple she 
came a week after the army raid 
the sikh secessionist campaign was launched by a small group of 
radicals in 1982 and exacerbated by the raid on the golden temple 
and by antisikh riots in northern india after mrs gandhis 
assassination 
at least 1200 people died in the army raid and the temple 
suffered heavy damage turning even moderate sikhs against the 
government at least 3000 sikhs were killed in ensuing riots 
sikhs easily identifiable by the their long hair flowing 
beards and colorful turbans form only 2 percent of indias 880 
million people but are a majority in punjab sikh militants say 
their community is discriminated against by the hindus who make up 
about 80 percent of the population 
