end run around the senate to install a new census director whose 
nomination had been languishing 
bush announced in houston for several speaking engagements 
said he would give barbara everitt byrant a recess appointment 
under the constitution an individual appointed by the president 
while the senate is on an extended recess can serve until the end 
of the following year without requiring senate confirmation 
since the everytenyears census is to be conducted next year 
bushs action would allow ms bryant to serve through the end of 
the 1990 census year with no further action by the senate 
ms bryant 63 of ann arbor mich was nominated by bush last 
sept 22 but when congress quit for the year last month her 
nomination still had not been acted on 
she succeeds john g keane as census director 
ms bryant for the past 12 years has been senior vice president 
of market opinion research of detroit the polling company founded 
by former bush campaign adviser robert teeter 
