institutions panel called on wall in a letter to revoke his 
agencys permission for the debt sales 
there is no need for me to recite the damage that this kind of 
sale caused to thousands of purchasers in the lincoln 
situation annunzio wrote 
wall in a talk to the association of government accountants 
said his agency was obligated to approve the debt sales under 
existing laws and rules 
there was no regulation that had been promulgated to prohibit 
it so we could not have disapproved it other than for good and 
other kinds of economic reasons he said 
the thrift agency is planning within weeks to adopt regulations 
sharply limiting future subordinated debt sales by sampls because 
weve learned from our experiences wall said 
bills restricting the sale of sampl debt have been introduced in 
the house by reps charles schumer dny and thomas mcmillen 
dmd 
