<TEXT>
the earth shook erupted collapsed caught fire and spawned 
vicious storms with regularity through the 1980s killing tens of 
thousands of people around the world but the decades cataclysms 
also included new forms of manmade tragedy 
here is a review of some of the decades worst disasters 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
may 18 1980 mount st helens volcano in washington state 
erupts with power equivalent to 500 hiroshima bombs this blast and 
two that followed within the next month killed 57 people and caused 
over 3 billion in damage 
oct 11 1980 earthquake in algeria kills 6000 and leaves 
400000 homeless 
nov 23 1980 more than 3000 killed and 300000 left homeless 
when earthquake europes deadliest in 65 years devastates 
southern italy 
may 2425 1985 cyclone out of bay of bengal comes ashore in 
bangladesh some 11000 killed 
sept 19 1985 earthquake strikes mexico city 7000 die 
nov 1314 1985 colombias erupting nevado del ruiz volcano 
melts snowcaps causing a massive mudflow that buries town of 
armero killing 25000 people 
aug 21 1986 cloud of toxic gas from volcanic lake nios in 
cameroon envelops several villages killing 1746 people and 
injuring 874 
may 7 1987 approximate start of series of chinese forest 
fires that kill 191 people 
sept 1216 1988 hurricane gilbert category 5 storm with 
winds up to 160 mph strikes jamaica cayman islands mexico and 
texas killing some 300 people 
oct 1925 1988 hurricane joanmiriam kills 184 in central 
america 
dec 7 1988 earthquake registering 69 on richter scale kills 
25000 in soviet armenia 
sept 1721 1989 hurricane hugo sweeps through caribbean and 
into charleston sc with 135 mph winds killing 62 
oct 17 1989 earthquake measuring 71 on richter scale 
rattles san francisco bay area killing 67 and causing estimated 7 
billion in property damage 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
aug 12 1985 in decades worst air disaster japan air lines 
747 crashes into a mountain near tokyo killing 520 four 
passengers survive crash 
dec 12 1985 arrow air charter dc8 crashes shortly after 
takeoff from gander newfoundland all 256 people aboard die 
including 248 us servicemen 
aug 16 1987 in decades worst us domestic plane crash 
northwest airlines md80 crashes on takeoff at detroit metropolitan 
airport killing 156 one passenger a 4yearold girl survives 
