two more foreign firms have been named as 
primary dealers in us government debt securities the federal 
reserve bank of new york announced 
the new york fed gave the approval wednesday to the new york 
branches of barclays de zoete wedd government securities inc a 
british firm and ubs securities inc a swiss firm 
primary dealers buy treasury bills notes and bonds directly 
from the government in regular auctions and then resell them to 
investors firms must show a history of participation in trading of 
government securities to qualify for the potentially lucrative 
primary dealership status 
the addition of the two firms brings the number of primary 
dealers to 44 including 15 foreign firms seven are japanese four 
are british and there is one apiece from canada australia hong 
kong and switzerland 
