<TEXT>
federal regulators have approved a 450 million 
capital infusion from pinnacle west capital corp to its troubled 
merabank subsidiary the thrifts chairman said late wednesday 
this is an important beginning of the recapitalization of 
merabank it means about 45 million a year in interest revenue 
said chairman gene rice 
however the chairman of the arizona corporation commission said 
the transfer was an ominous sign for arizona public serivce co 
the states largest public utility and pinnacle wests only 
profitable subsidiary for the past two years 
pinnacle west a 13 billionayear phoenixbased holding 
company was founded to run arizona public service on friday 
pacificorp a portland ore utility holding company announced it 
wanted to buy pinnacle west in a deal valued at about 187 billion 
the bid which is conditioned upon pinnacle west disposing of 
merabank is an expansion of an earlier offer from pacificorp to 
buy arizona public service pinnacle west created concern in 1986 
when it bought merabank just as the problems that have plagued us 
savings and loans became most acute 
the acquisition was criticized because of the possibility that 
the sampl could siphon funds from the utility company a robust 
dividendproducer pinnacle west has repeatedly denied any shifting 
of funds among its subsidiaries 
the settlement announced tonight saddles pinnacle west 
with additional debt at a time when the company can ill afford it 
and leaves ownership of merabank in the hands of pinnacle west with 
no assurance that losses will not continue to mount said renz 
jennings chairman of the corporation commission in a statement 
he said the regulatory commission was worried about the 
possibility that pinnacle west creditors will look to arizona 
public service co for repayment 
this commission has moved in the past to prevent the parent 
company from draining the resources of aps at the expense of 
ratepayers and the commission will do so again without 
hesitation or reservation jennings added 
pinnacle west chairman keith turley said the company and the 
federal office of thrift supervision office in san francisco agreed 
that pinnacle west will pay merabank 300 million in cash and 
accrued interest by march 31 1990 pinnacle west also said it will 
give the thrift an unsecured note for 150 million 
turley did not address the concerns over arizona public service 
pinnacle wests only company that falls under the direct purview of 
state regulators 
we also believe the state of arizona is well served by this 
resolution he said 
pinnacle west has obtained a commitment from chase manhattan 
bank chemical bank citibank and morgan guaranty trust co all of 
new york to lend the 300 million needed to come up with the first 
infusion in less than four months turley said 
he said the assumption of additional debt would require pinnacle 
west to renegotiate certain existing debt obligations for 
merabank a subsidiary it has placed on the sales block 
merabank lost 209 million in 1988 and 105 million in the first 
six months of this year with a projected loss of about the same 
amount in the last six months 
after a very difficult time over the past 18 months we 
believe this agreement is in the best interest of pinnacle west 
shareholders and will help reestablish the companys position in 
the financial community turley said 
